25/02/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police detained over 40 officials in a broad action against organised crime and corruption, at four border crossings -- Bogorodica, Medzitlija, Deve Bair and Tabanovce -- on Friday (February 23rd). The Interior Ministry says 26 of the suspects are border policemen, ten are customs officers and five are other staff. Over 38,000 euros in suspected bribes and other illegal activities were seized during searches. The Ministry says more arrests are possible. (Makfax, A1 TV, Telma TV, Utrinski Vesnik, Vest - 24/02/07)
